'''Noah Galloway''' is a [[United States Army]] soldier, model and athlete. He got injured in battle in Iraq, and lost his left arm and left leg. He is currently a contestant on ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' [[Dancing with the Stars<U+00A0>(U.S. season 20)|season 20]], paired with [[Sharna Burgess]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Noah Galloway |url=http://abc.go.com/shows/dancing-with-the-stars/cast/noah-galloway |work=[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]] |publisher=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |date=2015 |accessdate=March 23, 2015}}</ref>

==Military career==
A native of [[Birmingham]], [[Alabama]], Sergeant Noah Galloway was assigned to the 1st of the [[502nd Infantry]] of the [[101st Airborne Division]] out of [[Fort Campbell]], [[Kentucky]] during [[Operation Iraqi Freedom]]. 

Just three months in to his second tour of duty, he experienced a life changing injury. On December 19, 2005, Galloway lost two [[limb]]s: his left [[arm]] above the [[elbow]] and left [[leg]] above the knee in an [[improvised explosive device]] attack.<ref>{{cite web |first=Billy |last=Hallowell |title=U.S. Army Vet Who Lost Two Limbs Fighting in Iraq Absolutely Stuns <U+2018>Dancing With the Stars<U+2019> Audience, Leaving a Judge and Audience Members in Tears |url=http://www.theblaze.com/stories/2015/03/17/tears-flow-and-standing-ovations-abound-after-u-s-army-vet-who-lost-two-limbs-fighting-in-iraq-absolutely-stuns-dancing-with-the-stars-audience/ |work=[[TheBlaze]] |date=March 17, 2015 |accessdate=March 24, 2015}}</ref>
He was transported to Germany to receive medical treatment, remaining unconscious for five days. Galloway woke up late in the evening on [[Christmas Eve]] to learn he lost two of his limbs and sustained severe injuries to his right leg and his jaw. Galloway was then transferred to [[Walter Reed Army Medical Center]] in [[Washington, DC]].

==Motivational speaking==
Now a [[personal trainer]] and [[motivational speaker]], Galloway continues to compete, participating in adventure races around the country, such as Tough Mudder, Spartan events, [[crossfit]] competitions plus numerous 5K and 10K races.

A sought after public speaker, Galloway travels the country sharing his story, encouraging and motivating others to offer no excuses. From elementary school assemblies to veterans organizations to corporate sales meetings, Galloway<U+2019>s enthusiasm for life and his passion for helping others brings a unique perspective to gatherings.

==Modelling==
Most recently, Galloway appeared on the November cover of ''[[Men<U+2019>s Health]]'' magazine as he was named the publication<U+2019>s 2014 Ultimate Guy. He<U+2019>s also been a guest on numerous national talk shows including ''[[The Ellen Degeneres Show]]'' and ''[[The Today Show]]''. On October 2014, Galloway became the spokesman and model for [[Kenneth Cole]]'s new fragrance ''Mankind Ultimate''. 

=== ''Dancing with the Stars'' ===
He was chosen as a contestant on ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' [[Dancing with the Stars<U+00A0>(U.S. season 20)|season 20]], paired with [[Sharna Burgess]].

